fields.title: Sales by Quarter
fields.sql:
WITH SalesData AS (
    SELECT
        o.OrderID,
        strftime('%Y', o.OrderDate) AS Year,
        (strftime('%m', o.OrderDate) - 1) / 3 + 1 AS Quarter,
        od.UnitPrice * od.Quantity AS SalesAmount
    FROM
        Orders o
        JOIN "Order Details" od ON o.OrderID = od.OrderID
)

SELECT
    Year,
    Quarter,
    SUM(SalesAmount) AS TotalSales
FROM
    SalesData
GROUP BY
    Year,
    Quarter
ORDER BY
    Year,
    Quarter;

fields.title: Most popular products this quarter
fields.sql:
WITH SalesData AS (
    SELECT
        o.OrderID,
        strftime('%Y', o.OrderDate) AS Year,
        (strftime('%m', o.OrderDate) - 1) / 3 + 1 AS Quarter,
        od.ProductID,
        od.Quantity,
        od.UnitPrice * od.Quantity AS SalesAmount
    FROM
        Orders o
        JOIN "Order Details" od ON o.OrderID = od.OrderID
),
RecentQuarter AS (
    SELECT
        Year,
        Quarter
    FROM
        SalesData
    ORDER BY
        Year DESC,
        Quarter DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT
    sd.ProductID,
    p.ProductName,
    SUM(sd.Quantity) AS TotalQuantitySold,
    SUM(sd.SalesAmount) AS TotalSales
FROM
    SalesData sd
    JOIN RecentQuarter rq ON sd.Year = rq.Year AND sd.Quarter = rq.Quarter
    JOIN Products p ON sd.ProductID = p.ProductID
GROUP BY
    sd.ProductID,
    p.ProductName
ORDER BY
    TotalQuantitySold DESC;

fields.title: Rentals per category
fields.sql:
WITH rental_info AS (
    SELECT 
        r.rental_id,
        fc.category_id
    FROM 
        rental r
    JOIN 
        inventory i ON r.inventory_id = i.inventory_id
    JOIN 
        film_category fc ON i.film_id = fc.film_id
)
SELECT 
    c.name AS category_name,
    COUNT(ri.rental_id) AS rental_count
FROM 
    rental_info ri
JOIN 
    category c ON ri.category_id = c.category_id
GROUP BY 
    c.name
ORDER BY 
    rental_count DESC;

fields.title: Movie recommendations
fields.sql:
WITH rental_counts AS (
    SELECT
        f.film_id,
        f.title,
        fc.category_id,
        COUNT(r.rental_id) AS rental_count
    FROM
        rental r
        JOIN inventory i ON r.inventory_id = i.inventory_id
        JOIN film f ON i.film_id = f.film_id
        JOIN film_category fc ON f.film_id = fc.film_id
    GROUP BY
        f.film_id,
        fc.category_id
),
popular_films AS (
    SELECT
        film_id,
        title,
        category_id,
        rental_count,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY category_id ORDER BY rental_count DESC) AS rn
    FROM
        rental_counts
)
SELECT
    film_id,
    title
FROM
    popular_films
WHERE
    rn <= 3 -- Limit to the most popular few films per category
ORDER BY
    RANDOM() -- Randomly select 3 films
LIMIT 3;
fields.description: please recommend 3 movies i might want to watch. Look at the most popular few movies from each category (based on # of rentals) and then recommend a random set, so that i get some different suggestions each time i refresh.

fields.title: Store rental rankings
fields.sql:
WITH StoreRentals AS (
    SELECT
        i.store_id,
        COUNT(r.rental_id) AS rental_count
    FROM
        rental r
        INNER JOIN inventory i ON r.inventory_id = i.inventory_id
    GROUP BY
        i.store_id
)
SELECT
    s.store_id,
    s.manager_staff_id,
    s.address_id,
    sr.rental_count
FROM
    StoreRentals sr
    INNER JOIN store s ON sr.store_id = s.store_id
ORDER BY
    sr.rental_count DESC;
fields.description: what are the most successful stores? Which rent the most movies?

fields.title: Cross category actors
fields.sql:
WITH actor_category_count AS (
    SELECT
        fa.actor_id,
        a.first_name,
        a.last_name,
        COUNT(DISTINCT fc.category_id) AS category_count
    FROM
        film_actor fa
        JOIN actor a ON fa.actor_id = a.actor_id
        JOIN film_category fc ON fa.film_id = fc.film_id
    GROUP BY
        fa.actor_id,
        a.first_name,
        a.last_name
)
SELECT
    actor_id,
    first_name,
    last_name,
    category_count
FROM
    actor_category_count
WHERE
    category_count = (SELECT MAX(category_count) FROM actor_category_count);
fields.description: What actors work across the most categories of movie?

fields.title: Prompt length analysis
fields.sql:
WITH LengthStats AS (
    SELECT
        AVG(LENGTH(prompt)) AS mean_length,
        AVG(LENGTH(prompt) * LENGTH(prompt)) - AVG(LENGTH(prompt)) * AVG(LENGTH(prompt)) AS variance
    FROM 
        explorer_promptlog
)
SELECT 
    mean_length AS average_length,
    SQRT(variance) AS length_variability
FROM 
    LengthStats;
fields.description: What is the average lenght of prompts? How much variability is there?

fields.title: Customer Demographics
fields.sql:
SELECT 
    cust.CustomerID, 
    cust.CompanyName, 
    cd.CustomerTypeID, 
    cd.CustomerDesc
FROM 
    CustomerCustomerDemo ccd
JOIN 
    CustomerDemographics cd ON ccd.CustomerTypeID = cd.CustomerTypeID
JOIN 
    Customers cust ON ccd.CustomerID = cust.CustomerID;

fields.title: Employee sales performance
fields.sql:
WITH EmployeeSales AS (
    SELECT 
        o.EmployeeID, 
        SUM(od.UnitPrice * od.Quantity) AS TotalSales
    FROM 
        Orders o
    JOIN 
        "Order Details" od ON o.OrderID = od.OrderID
    GROUP BY 
        o.EmployeeID
)
SELECT 
    e.EmployeeID, 
    e.LastName, 
    e.FirstName, 
    e.Title, 
    es.TotalSales
FROM 
    EmployeeSales es
JOIN 
    Employees e ON es.EmployeeID = e.EmployeeID
ORDER BY 
    es.TotalSales DESC;
fields.description: Who are our best employees, based on sales?

fields.title: Longest running queries

    sql,
    AVG(duration) AS average_duration
FROM 
    explorer_querylog

    sql
ORDER BY 
    average_duration DESC;

WITH TopGenres AS (
    SELECT c.category_id, c.name, COUNT(fc.film_id) AS film_count
    FROM category c
    JOIN film_category fc ON c.category_id = fc.category_id
    GROUP BY c.category_id, c.name
    ORDER BY film_count DESC
    LIMIT 3 -- Adjust this number to get more or fewer top genres
),
FilmsInTopGenres AS (
    SELECT fc.film_id, fc.category_id
    FROM film_category fc
    JOIN TopGenres tg ON fc.category_id = tg.category_id
),
ActorsInTopGenres AS (
    SELECT fa.actor_id, fc.category_id
    FROM film_actor fa
    JOIN FilmsInTopGenres fc ON fa.film_id = fc.film_id
),
ActorPopularity AS (
    SELECT 
        a.actor_id,
        a.first_name || ' ' || a.last_name AS actor_name,
        ag.category_id,
        COUNT(ag.actor_id) AS film_count
    FROM actor a
    JOIN ActorsInTopGenres ag ON a.actor_id = ag.actor_id
    GROUP BY a.actor_id, a.first_name, a.last_name, ag.category_id
)
SELECT 
    ap.actor_name,
    tg.name AS genre_name,
    ap.film_count
FROM ActorPopularity ap
JOIN TopGenres tg ON ap.category_id = tg.category_id
ORDER BY tg.name, ap.film_count DESC;

    JOIN TopGenres tg ON fc.category_id = tg.category_id
),
ActorsInTopGenres AS (
    SELECT fa.actor_id, fc.category_id
    FROM film_actor fa
    JOIN FilmsInTopGenres fc ON fa.film_id = fc.film_id
),
ActorRentals AS (
    SELECT 
        ar.actor_id,
        fc.category_id,
        COUNT(re.rental_id) AS rental_count
    FROM rental re
    JOIN inventory i ON re.inventory_id = i.inventory_id
    JOIN film_actor fa ON i.film_id = fa.film_id
    JOIN FilmsInTopGenres fc ON fa.film_id = fc.film_id
    JOIN ActorsInTopGenres ar ON fa.actor_id = ar.actor_id AND fc.category_id = ar.category_id
    GROUP BY ar.actor_id, fc.category_id
),
ActorPopularity AS (
    SELECT 
        a.actor_id,
        a.first_name || ' ' || a.last_name AS actor_name,
        ar.category_id,
        ar.rental_count
    FROM actor a
    JOIN ActorRentals ar ON a.actor_id = ar.actor_id
)
SELECT 
    ap.actor_name,
    tg.name AS genre_name,
    ap.rental_count
FROM ActorPopularity ap
JOIN TopGenres tg ON ap.category_id = tg.category_id
ORDER BY tg.name, ap.rental_count DESC;

SELECT Customers.CustomerID, Customers.CompanyName, Customers.Country, ISNULL(SUM([Order Subtotals].Subtotal), 0) AS [Customer Total], ISNULL(SUM(CONVERT(money, [1997].Payments/100)*100),0) AS [1997]
FROM Customers
LEFT JOIN Orders ON Orders.CustomerID = Customers.CustomerID
LEFT JOIN [Order Details] ON [Order Details].OrderID = Orders.OrderID
LEFT JOIN [Order Subtotals] ON [Order Subtotals].OrderID = Orders.OrderID
LEFT JOIN (SELECT Customers.CustomerID, Customers.CompanyName, Customers.Country, ([Order Details].UnitPrice * [Order Details].Quantity * (1.0- [Order Details].Discount)) AS [Payments]
			FROM Customers
			INNER JOIN Orders ON Orders.CustomerID = Customers.CustomerID
			INNER JOIN [Order Details] ON [Order Details].OrderID = Orders.OrderID
			WHERE YEAR(Orders.OrderDate) = '1997') AS [1997] 
ON [1997].CustomerID = Customers.CustomerID
GROUP BY Customers.CustomerID, Customers.CompanyName, Customers.Country
ORDER BY [Customer Total]

    LIMIT 1
)

    JOIN RecentQuarter rq ON sd.Year = rq.Year AND sd.Quarter = rq.Quarter
    JOIN Products p ON sd.ProductID = p.ProductID
GROUP BY
    sd.ProductID,
    p.ProductName
ORDER BY
    TotalQuantitySold DESC;

WITH rental_info AS (
    SELECT 
        r.rental_id,
        fc.category_id
    FROM 
        rental r
    JOIN 
        inventory i ON r.inventory_id = i.inventory_id
    JOIN 
        film_category fc ON i.film_id = fc.film_id
)
SELECT 
    c.name AS category_name,
    COUNT(ri.rental_id) AS rental_count
FROM 
    rental_info ri
JOIN 
    category c ON ri.category_id = c.category_id
GROUP BY 
    c.name
ORDER BY 
    rental_count DESC;

WITH rental_counts AS (
    SELECT
        f.film_id,
        f.title,
        fc.category_id,
        COUNT(r.rental_id) AS rental_count
    FROM
        rental r
        JOIN inventory i ON r.inventory_id = i.inventory_id
        JOIN film f ON i.film_id = f.film_id
        JOIN film_category fc ON f.film_id = fc.film_id
    GROUP BY
        f.film_id,
        fc.category_id
),
popular_films AS (
    SELECT
        film_id,
        title,
        category_id,
        rental_count,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY category_id ORDER BY rental_count DESC) AS rn
    FROM
        rental_counts
)
SELECT
    film_id,
    title
FROM
    popular_films

    rn <= 3 -- Limit to the most popular few films per category

    RANDOM() -- Randomly select 3 films

WITH SalesData AS (
    SELECT
        o.OrderID,
        strftime('%Y', o.OrderDate) AS Year,
        (strftime('%m', o.OrderDate) - 1) / 3 + 1 AS Quarter,
        od.ProductID,
        od.Quantity,
        od.UnitPrice * od.Quantity AS SalesAmount
    FROM
        Orders o
        JOIN "Order Details" od ON o.OrderID = od.OrderID
),
RecentQuarter AS (
    SELECT
        Year,
        Quarter
    FROM
        SalesData
    ORDER BY
        Year DESC,
        Quarter DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT
    sd.ProductID,
    p.ProductName,
    SUM(sd.Quantity) AS TotalQuantitySold,
    SUM(sd.SalesAmount) AS TotalSales
FROM
    SalesData sd
    JOIN RecentQuarter rq ON sd.Year = rq.Year AND sd.Quarter = rq.Quarter
    JOIN Products p ON sd.ProductID = p.ProductID
GROUP BY
    sd.ProductID,
    p.ProductName
ORDER BY
    TotalQuantitySold DESC;
